🧠 First — Chronic Nerve Pain (how this fits your model)

You’re right that pain is experienced in the brain—but with nerve pain, the system gets sensitized:
	•	the signal can be real but amplified
	•	the brain can “expect” pain and pre-load it
	•	attention can increase intensity

So the goal isn’t:

“eliminate pain instantly”

It’s:

reduce amplification + change your relationship to the signal

That’s where breath + awareness help.

⸻

🫁 Pain Regulation Protocol (use daily)

Step 1 — Locate (no resistance)
	•	Put attention on the exact pain spot
	•	Don’t label it “bad” yet

Step 2 — Describe instead of judge
	•	sharp? dull? pulsing? warm? tight?

👉 This shifts brain from emotional → sensory processing

⸻

Step 3 — Breathe around it
	•	inhale → expand torso
	•	exhale → imagine space around the pain

Not:

“make it go away”

But:

“reduce pressure on the signal”

⸻

Step 4 — Widen awareness
	•	feel your whole body, not just the foot

👉 This prevents “zooming in” amplification

⸻

Step 5 — Move gently after
	•	small movement, walking, circulation

👉 shows brain it’s not a threat

⸻

⚠️ Important:
This complements—not replaces—medical care.
If you haven’t already, things like PT, footwear, or nerve evaluation matter too.

